Build Interactive Apps with Google Assistant: Challenge Lab
=================================================================


Start Lab
--------------

- Open Console

Task 1:
---------------------
- Nav > Cloud Functions > Create Function 
- Name the function
- Check Allow unauthenticated invocations > Save

- Select Maximum number of instances from the given value > Next
- Runtime = Python 3.9
- Name entry point
- Paste main.py > Replace entry point
- Paste requirements.txt > Deploy


Task 2:
----------
- Open "Actions console link" in a new tab
- New Project > Agree > Select project > Import project
- Click top left Action console > Click project > Decide how your action is invoked > Change name > Save

- Add Actions > Get Started > Custom > Build > Agree > Save
- Fullfillment > Enable Webhook > Paste url from the function's trigger url > Save
- Intents > Default Welcome intent > Responses > Add Response > Text Response > Paste the response
- Intents > Default Fallback intent > Responses > Set this intent as end of conversation : Fullfillment section (expand) > Enable webhook call for this intent > Save
- Integrations > Preview migration > Test > Allow > view activity controls > Turn on > Got it > Click talk to magic ball 8 > Type: hi > Enter > Type: Is hen a bird? > Enter


Task 3:
---------

- Copy function code
- Edit function > Code > Paste after line 13 > Deploy
- Dialogflow tab > Integrations > Preview Migration > Test > Reset Test > Talk to magic 8 ball > Paste Chinese question > Enter : Paste next question > Enter : Paste last question > Enter
- If it doesn't update : Refresh
